<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ul>
<li>
<p><span data-colorid=3D"ot6hakccw5">Menu (gear) button pressed</span></p><=
/li>
</ul></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span data-colorid=3D"wsfaergy3q">If current source is a game, I would l=
ike to see the game bar instead of Quick menu when MENU key pressed. </span=
></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">4</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Default setting</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>The default selected setting is Picture Mode if no selection previously =
made. Thereafter Quick Settings launches with the last used setting selecte=
d.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">5</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Navigation</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>As a user, I want to quickly and easily navigate Quick settings.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Up/Down moves to the next/previous setting in Quick Settings.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Up/Down wraps. Press Down from the last setting wraps up to Picture Mode=
. Press Up from Picture Mode wraps down to the All Settings.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Last setting will be All Settings and Help.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Left/Right moves to the next/previous option for the selected setting.</=
p></li>
<li>
<p>Up/Down/Left/Right also stops BT pairing if in progress and continues wi=
th the selection.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Press OK to deep dive to the setting (All Settings, Accessibility, Pair =
Headphones if not paired, Network from dynamic if not connected)</p></li>
<li>
<p>Press Back from All Settings, Accessibility, Gaming or Help deep dive or=
 Bluetooth Headphones deep dive returns to Quick settings. If Help is selec=
ted from Quick settings the deep dive goes to Support Code so Back then ret=
urns to Help in Quick Settings.</p></li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">6</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Picture Mode</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>switches in quick</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>User wants to change picture mode quickly based on viewing conditions or=
 content.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Asterisk to indicate picture mode changes included.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Picture mode banks do not display in Quick (as adjustments only possible=
 in All Settings).</p></li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">7</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Pair Headphones OR Bluetooth Headphones</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>HYBRID:</p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>paired then switches in quick</p></li>
<li>
<p>Never paired then deep dive to BT Headphones</p></li>
</ol></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>As a user, I want to</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Setting name if no paired headphones is =E2=80=9CPair Headphones=E2=80=
=9D</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>No paired devices, press OK to deep link to Bluetooth Headphones to pair=
</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>Setting name after one Bluetooth headphones is paired is =E2=80=9CBlueto=
oth Headphones=E2=80=9D</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>If headphones paired then toggle between options using left/right</p></l=
i>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>Press OK to activate the selected option. OK connects paired headphones,=
 disconnects (if Off selected) or deep links to Pair Headphones</p></li>
<li>
<p>Current setting is BTHeadphonesName (connected), press Right, order is</=
p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Off</p></li>
<li>
<p>BTHeadphonesName last used1</p></li>
<li>
<p>BTHeadphonesName last used2</p></li>
<li>
<p>Pair new Headphones</p></li>
<li>
<p>BTHeadphonesName connected (indicated by checkmark)</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>Current Setting is BTHeadphonesName (connected), press Left, order is</p=
>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Pair new Headphones</p></li>
<li>
<p>BTHeadphonesName last used2</p></li>
<li>
<p>BTHeadphonesName last used1</p></li>
<li>
<p>Off</p></li>
<li>
<p>BTHeadphonesName connected (indicated by a checkmark)</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>If headphones connected and</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Headphones setting in focus (highlighted), display checkmark next to nam=
e</p></li>
<li>
<p>Headphones setting not in focus (not highlighted), then no display of ch=
eckmark, only name displays</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>If paired headphones are not connected then default setting is Off.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Press Right then order is</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>BTHeadphonesName last used1</p></li>
<li>
<p>BTHeadphonesName last used2</p></li>
<li>
<p>Pair Headphones</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>Press Left then order is</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Pair new Headphones</p></li>
<li>
<p>BTHeadphonesName last used2</p></li>
<li>
<p>BTHeadphonesName last used1</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>Paired headphones connecting errors:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>BTHeadphonesName is selected</p></li>
<li>
<p>Press OK to Connect</p></li>
<li>
<p>If turned off or not available</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Display unable to connect message (requirement below)</p></li>
<li>
<p>BTHeadphonesName remains selected but audio again heard from TV system a=
udio (TV Speakers or sound bar)</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>Never paired then BT Headphones has no setting below the title. Press OK=
 key to deep link to BT Headphones submenu to support initial pairing. Righ=
t/Left keys- no action</p></li>
<li>
<p>Connecting BT headphones typically takes about 2 seconds but if can take=
 up to 5 seconds or longer. During that time</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>During connection the BT headphones setting is replaced with =E2=80=9CCo=
nnecting=E2=80=9D and the name of headphones.</p></li>
<li>
<p>A press of Up/Down navigates Quick Settings and continues to connect the=
 headphones.</p></li>
<li>
<p>A press of Right/Left allows user to move to other settings. A press OK =
with =E2=80=9COff=E2=80=9D setting stops connection to headphones. A press =
OK with another pair of headphones, drops connection of first pair of headp=
hones and connects to selected pair.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Display error notification if connection fails after 15 seconds as per B=
T audio requirements</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>If sku does not support BT Headphones then setting does not display and =
all settings move up one.</p></li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">8</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>BT Headphones unable to connect message (only appears if the device has =
BT capability)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Select paired device</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Connection Unsuccessful</p>
<p>Make sure =E2=80=9C[Device Name]=E2=80=9C is turned on and in range.</p>
<p>OK to dismiss<br>
Tray Again to retry connection</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">9</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Closed Captions</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>switches on/off in quick</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>User wants to enable/disable closed captions quickly</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>CC key no longer on remote (replaced by special function key)</p></li>
<li>
<p>Supports CVAA requirements for users that have hearing disability</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Easy on/off for mixed household of hearing/hearing disabled</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>Supports Antenna</p></li>
<li>
<p>Supports apps (e.g. Netflix, Amazon, Hulu, WatchFree+) with content that=
 includes closed captions.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Some users enable/disable CC though not hearing impaired.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Some users will enable once. Some users will enable/disable frequently.<=
/p></li>
<li>
<p>If source is HDMI, setting does not change and a notification displays t=
o enable CC from the device.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Notification displays at screen bottom with OK key to dismiss. Asset lay=
out same as for failed Headphones notification. =E2=80=9CCheck the closed c=
aptioning setting on your HDMI device connected to this TV.=E2=80=9D</p></l=
i>
</ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">10</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Sleep Timer</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>switches in quick</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>User wants to turn off sleep timer due to power off notification.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>easy access to turn off or reset sleep timer</p></li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">11</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Gaming</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Deep dive to Gaming</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Deep links into the Gaming menu with Game Controller highlighted for all=
 sources including VIZIO Home and apps as well as Antenna and WatchFree+</p=
></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">12</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Accessibility</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Deep Dive to Accessibility</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>User wants to enable or disable accessibility functions including but no=
t limited to CC</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>As per CVAA, easy access to required Accessibility including</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Closed Captions</p></li>
<li>
<p>Video Description</p></li>
<li>
<p>Talk Back</p></li>
<li>
<p>Zoom Mode</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>Selection of Accessibility direct links into Accessibility in the sideba=
r</p></li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">13</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>All settings</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Deep dive to main menu</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>User wants to access settings not included in Quick</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Selection of All Settings direct links into Settings in the sidebar.</p>=
</li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd">14</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Help</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Deep dive to Support Code page.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
